The paper deals with interference modeling in wireless networks, which is a common topic in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the formation of holes in the interference field, which is related to the Spatial Interactions (cs.SI) sub-category. The use of bounds and approximations to analyze the interference field is a common technique in the Mathematical Aspects of Computer Science (cs.MA) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the coverage probability of the typical node, which is related to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category.
